  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the efficiency of a rapid diagnostic test (Paracheck
      Pf) for the diagnosis of uncomplicated Plasmodium falciparum malaria by community health
      workers at village level in Tanzania and how the use of rapid diagnostic test may influence
      prescription of antimalarial drugs.

      The hypothesis is that rapid diagnostic tests used by community health workers will reduce
      the use of antimalarial drugs (Coartem; Novartis) by 30% without affecting the health
      outcome.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
